title: Katherine Ryan claims alleged TV predator is a 'perpetrator of sexual assault' in shock interview
description: Katherine Ryan has said the man she accused of being a sexual predator has committed sexual assault - but she cannot reveal his name for legal reasons

title: Girl, 11, tells parents she suffered school bullying from racists
description: Dalaya Hooper's mother Dawnetta took to social media to show off what her daughter had been through at Riverwood Middle School in Clayton.

title: Matt Hancock faces being barred from standing in next election
description: By December 5, Tory MPs have to tell their party headquarters if they want to apply again to stand in their current seat or a new constituency for the next election.

title: Migrants employed as security guards at Doha park 'paid 35p an hour and get one day off a month'
description: The security staff that are deployed across Al Bidda Park, a sprawling green space linked to the Fifa Fan Festival, claim to work 12-hour days and only get one day off a month.

title: King Charles 'set to axe a number of staff at Windsor Castle in the coming weeks'
description: As part of a radical overhaul of staffing across royal residences staff at the castle fear they may be made redundant before the New Year, the Mirror revealed late on Friday evening.

title: Ukrainian refugees on SNP ferry have endured tiny cabins, visa woes crew since JULY
description: Ukrainian families who escaped Russia's deadly invasion of their country have been housed on a cruise ship docked in Edinburgh since July.

title: PLATELL'S PEOPLE: Are Michelle Obama and Meghan Markle true feminists or did they just marry well?
description: AMANDA PLATELL: Given that Michelle Obama sold 14 million copies of her book Becoming, inevitably she now has a new literary offering.

title: Matthew Guy disowns Victorian Liberal candidate over links to controversial church
description: Liberal leader Matthew Guy said some of Renee Heath's views were not uncovered through the party's candidate review process before she was preselected.

title: Billy Connolly reveals the secret to being funny: Stay off booze and drugs before you go on stage
description: Scottish comedian Sir Billy Connolly, 79, told how he risked his own career by drinking too much and advised young comics to steer clear.

title: Why we're POWERLESS to stop wind farms: Testimonies from people forced to live in turbine shadows
description: Every so often a glossy pamphlet pops through the letter boxes in the Kirkcudbrightshire village of Carsphairn. It gives residents (local Nigel Martin pictured) news on a new wind farm.

title: Croc spotting: Crocodile spotted by family in Wenlock River near Cape York, Queensland
description: Jeremaine Agale shared an ominous photo of the Wenlock River near Cape York at Queensland's northern tip on the Cape York Information Facebook page on Thursday alongside a dire warning.

title: Alec Baldwin texted widower of cinematographer he shot and killed suggesting gun loaded in SABOTAGE
description: Alec Baldwin, 64, sent a series of text messages in the days and weeks following the fatal shooting of cinematographer Halyna Hutchins to her widow suggesting 'sabotage' is the cause.

title: Union boss in NHS 'maximum disruption' row
description: Colenzo Jarrett-Thorpe is claimed to have said the public will support his members even if 'maximum disruption might lead to harm or even death'.

title: Westpac scam: Father-of-two lost his life savings in a 'brilliant' scam
description: Father-of-two Waine Sauermann from NSW lost $27,380 and was left with just three dollars in his account after he was fooled by scammers into handing over financial information.

title: Tokyo is the city of turtlenecks: Governor urges city residents to wear jumpers to reduce energy use
description: The governor of Tokyo has urged the city's residents to wear turtleneck jumpers to reduce energy consumption over winter. Yuriko Koike (pictured) said turtlenecks could help reduce energy bill rises.

title: I'm A Celebrity winner Jacqueline Jossa's husband Dan Osborne 'held on suspicion of GBH'
description: TOWIE's Dan Osborne, the husband of EastEnders and I'm A Celeb star Jacqueline Jossa, was held on suspicion of GBH after allegedly breaking a party guest's jaw

title: BBC stars in Qatar have been given a 'cheat sheet' for tricky questions on Qatar controversies
description: In guidance sent to its army of pundits, presenters and commentators, the broadcaster says it will address the controversy in its coverage.

title: Diversity's iconic Children in Need 2022 performance
description: The 2022 Children In Need telethon returned to BBC One on Friday evening,  live from the BBC studios in Salford.

title: Forget Moet! Own-label fizz from Aldi, Tesco and Waitrose beats some of the most-celebrated houses
description: Moet & Chandon, at £39 a bottle, was beaten by Tesco Finest Premier Cru Champagne, £23, and Waitrose Blanc de Blancs Brut, £25.99, which tied top with scores of 82 per cent.

title: Naomi Biden's sisters Maisy and Finnegan get glammed up for rehearsal dinner
description: Naomi Biden's younger sisters Maisy and Finnegan got glammed up to join President Joe Biden, Jill Biden, the bride and groom at a rehearsal dinner ahead of Saturday's big White House wedding.

title: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Prove to the strivers you're on their side
description: DAILY MAIL COMMENT: Beleaguered families were already groaning under the highest tax burden since the 1950s. Steepling gas prices and food inflation in recent months have further strained their budgets.

title: Eton College apologises after 'girls on visit from state school were taunted with racial slurs'
description: Several pupils have been 'sanctioned' according to the school after an investigation into an incident during a speech by former Ukip leader Nigel Farage.

title: AMA doctors warning about resistant 'superbugs' making basic cuts deadly for hospital patients
description: AMA Professor Steve Robson urges Australia to create a Centre for Disease Control like the US to manage increasing risks posed by antimicrobial resistant superbugs.

title: Watching your team can be bad for your heart - but hugs make it better -scientists discover
description: Experts at the University Hospital Schleswig-Holstein in Germany studied the hearts of 52 healthy men and 18 with known cardiovascular disease as they followed Euros games last year.

title: Idaho cops release map of murdered students' last movements and beg witnesses to come forward
description: Police on Friday released a map showing the last known movements of the four students found dead in their shared home in Moscow, Idaho. Their two roommates have not been ruled out as suspects.

title: Top Navy officer arrested for 'sexually assaulting young sailor' hours before misconduct training
description: A high-ranking Royal Navy submariner (file photo) has been arrested after being accused of attacking a junior rate after allegedly imprisoning him following a night of drinking at a naval base this month.

title: JANE FRYER: Will King Charles help save the magical gas lamps threatened by council numbskulls?
description: JANE FRYER: Aran Osman is perched 12 ft up a ladder on a dark and drizzly evening in Central London, fiddling about with a 100-year-old gas lamp in the gloom.

title: David Walsh reveals how he pulled off biggest gamble and won $60million German lotto
description: David Walsh, who founded popular Tasmanian art gallery MONA, said he was part of a syndicate that had spent $11million to purchase one million tickets in the lottery six months ago.

title: MISS MONEYSAVER helps you with the cost of living crunch
description: JASMINE BIRTLES: When we were children, my brother and I loved power cuts. We had a coal fire in the lounge and we used it for toasting bread and even cooking boiled eggs.

title: Toxic culture in the health unions trying to bring the NHS to its knees this winter
description: A new wave of militancy is sweeping through the NHS. Despite the extra funding  just announced by the Chancellor, a winter of discontent now beckons for our ailing health service.

title: Weather forecast: Cold front to bring snow to Tasmania, low temps in Victoria, SA and NSW
description: Southern Australia will feel the cold from Monday with temperatures in Victoria, Tasmania and southern NSW expected to peak at just 15C.
